JOHANNESBURG – Hugh Masekela was honoured with a musical tribute at the University of Johannesburg (UJ)'s Soweto Campus on Sunday. Various musicians performed at this final public tribute to the legendary artist, activist and composer. READ: How did Mark Fish get Hugh Masekela wrong? Some of the artists were people who have worked with Masekela. A series of events had been staged to remember Masekela’s life. Bra Hugh, as he was affectionately known, died on 23 January after a long battle with prostate cancer. Masekela will be buried in a private funeral, as per his wishes, at a date still to be determined. eNCA